# Git / GitHub PR state ‚Äî sync before advice

**Problem:** Chat context can still say ‚Äúopen PR #80‚Äù after #80 merged and #81 exists. The assistant has **no live GitHub view** unless commands run **in this session**.

## When this applies

- Before advising **merge**, **‚Äúwhat‚Äôs next‚Äù** after a PR, or **which PR** to open.
- Before pasting or opening a **PR URL** or number after `gh pr create`.
- When the user says they **just merged** ‚Äî **do not** assume local `main` is current.

## Minimum refresh (pick at least one)

| Action                     | Command / script                                          |
| --------                   | ------------------                                        |
| Update remote refs         | `git fetch origin`                                        |
| Align local `main`         | `git checkout main` ‚Üí `git pull origin main`              |
| Verify a PR                | `gh pr view <n> --json number,state,mergedAt,url`         |
| List PR for current branch | `gh pr list --head <branch-name> --json number,state,url` |

Prefer repo automation when it already does fetch/rebase: **`.\scripts\commit-or-pr.ps1`** (see `.cursor/skills/token-aware-automation/SKILL.md` and `CONTRIBUTING.md` ¬ß PR state).

## Long-lived branches and conflict control

- **Commit locally** in small, themed chunks (see `.cursor/rules/execution-priority-and-pr-batching.mdc` ‚Äî commit cadence) so progress is **recorded** and diffs stay reviewable.
- **Integrate `main` often** on feature branches (`merge` or `rebase` after `git fetch`) so you do not open a PR or cut a release with a **weeks-old** base and a wall of conflicts.
- Before **PR / publish / release**: `git status` clean or intentional; run **`check-all`** (or agreed subset); use **Preview** (`commit-or-pr.ps1 -Action Preview`) so scope matches intent.

## After creating a PR

1. Run `gh pr view --json number,state,url` (or `gh pr list --head <branch>`).
1. **Only then** share the link or say ‚ÄúPR #N‚Äù ‚Äî avoids pointing at the **previous** merged PR.

## GitHub lag

Right after merge, `gh` may still show `OPEN` briefly. Re-run `gh pr view` or wait a few seconds; distinguish **UI lag** from **stale chat context**.

## Human + agent habit

Maintainers: after merging on GitHub, run **`git checkout main && git pull`**. Agents: **run a refresh command** before merge-related advice unless the user pasted fresh `gh`/`git` output in the same turn.
